On International Women's Day, the article highlights the important contributions women make to global prosperity, security, government, and innovation. The Women's Global Development and Prosperity Initiative (W-GDP) was launched by the Administration last year with the goal of reaching 50 million women in the developing world by 2025. The initiative recognizes that empowering women leads to more prosperous and peaceful societies. The article also mentions the Women, Peace, and Security Act of 2017, which promotes the meaningful inclusion of women in economic, political, and social life to minimize conflict and build peace. In the United States, women are playing a central role in the economic revival, with the unemployment rate for women reaching its lowest in 65 years. Women now comprise a majority of the American workforce, contributing to the prosperity of the country's communities. The article emphasizes the commitment of the United States to promoting equal opportunity for all women.